  "text": "Here f may not be given explicitly, and an efficient implementation of algorithms requires that certain queries related to f can be answered in time polynomial in n. We will consider later implementation details. In the application discussed here, relevant polynomial time oracles are available via min-cut computations. In particular, we have a polynomial time separation oracle for the LP-relaxation due to Frank and Jordán [CITATION_1] :",
